Eyes: Ocular paralysis, hemianopsia, disturbed pupillary reaction, optic neuritis and atrophy, subconjunctival and retinal hemorrhages
Head: Jaws firmly clenched
Trismus
Roaring ears
Inclination to turn in a circle
Heaviness of head
Sticking pain in temples
Cerebral congestion; hallucination of vision, hearing and touch
Skin: Anaesthesia; vesication along course of nerves; herpes zoster; pemphigus, with large and small vesicles

details: Herpes zoster, pemphigus, and trismus are produced by this drug. Coldness, SLEEPINESS, loss of consciousness are marked. Vertigo.
name: Carboneum oxygenisatum
